Backport of XSS fix from BackupPC master (commit 58b0bb4, Nov 2025).

The CGI View action passed the user-supplied `num` query parameter into the
page without HTML escaping. The fix wraps it in EscHTML(). Originally fixed in
2012, accidentally dropped in 3.3.0 (2013), tracked by Debian maintainers for
years, and re-applied upstream for the 4.4.1 release.

Remove this patch once BACKUPPC_VERSION is bumped to 4.4.1.

--- a/lib/BackupPC/CGI/View.pm
+++ b/lib/BackupPC/CGI/View.pm
@@ -47,7 +47,7 @@ sub action
     my $compress   = 0;
     my $fh;
     my $host      = $In{host};
-    my $num       = $In{num};
+    my $num       = ${EscHTML($In{num})};
     my $type      = $In{type};
     my $linkHosts = 0;
     my($file, $comment);
